  Earlier this week Mandela said that the country was in dire of leaders who have moral values and integrity and will uphold the constitution.Mandela was speaking during a Freedom Movement rally in Pretoria at which political leaders reiterated a call to President Jacob Zuma to step down. It was held to coincide with Freedom Day, which marked the anniversary of the country's first democratic elections in 1994.* This UpFront interview with Ndileka Mandela aired on Friday night. For more information, follow UpFront on Twitter: @AJUpFront. Al Jazeera and ANA  